{
  "texts": [
    "In Wordflow, a prompt template includes pre-defined prefix text and a placeholder for the input text.",
    "For example, the prefix text can be \"Improve the flow of the following text\".",
    "The input placeholder in the template serves as a variable that will be substituted with the selected text from the editor.",
    "Inspired by popular prompting tools such as LangChain [13] Fig. 3: The Prompt Editor allows users to easily configure LLM settings such as temperature and output parsing rules.and PromptMaker [30], our tool supports basic prompt templating.",
    "Users can include a special string {{text}} in their prompt template to represent the input placeholder (Fig. 2B), which will be replaced with the selected text from the editor before running the prompt."
  ]
}